The paper deals with simplicial homology, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses linear programming, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The results on computing optimal homologous chains are related to topological data analysis, which falls under the scope of computational topology (cs.GT). Finally, the paper's focus on edge contractions and their effect on homology groups suggests that it could also be relevant to algorithms for graph and network analysis (cs.SI).
